the president would say about
his much-awaited announcement.

01:46.800 --> 01:51.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Earlier in the day, however,
the head of the Environmental
Protection Agency, Scott Pruitt,

01:51.566 --> 01:53.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
delivered an energetic defense.

01:53.666 --> 01:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT PRUITT, Environmental
Protection Agency Administrator:
We have nothing to be apologetic

01:55.633 --> 01:57.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about as a country.

01:57.400 --> 02:02.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We have reduced our
CO2 footprint to levels
of the early 1990s.

02:02.033 --> 02:06.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's been largely
accomplished through innovation
and technology, not government

02:06.433 --> 02:08.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
mandate.

02:08.466 --> 02:12.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Nevertheless,
the announcement has touched off
a chorus of protest both here

02:13.166 --> 02:15.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the U.S. and abroad.

02:15.300 --> 02:17.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
