Putin said continued dialogue
was necessary at an event

04:12.433 --> 04:15.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
moderated by NBC News
anchor Megyn Kelly.

04:15.100 --> 04:18.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
VLADIMIR PUTIN, Russian
President (through
translator): Rather
than make noise over it,

04:18.466 --> 04:23.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we need to create conditions
for mutual work, because if
countries that are big emitters,

04:25.433 --> 04:29.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
like the United States, will
not take part at all, it will
be impossible to negotiate

04:29.900 --> 04:31.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and sign any kind of agreement.

04:31.900 --> 04:36.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back at the White
House, the EPA's Pruitt said
the president has made clear

04:36.133 --> 04:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he's willing to work with
anyone on a better deal.

04:39.933 --> 04:44.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
