in a town of 6,000, and most
of the town doesn't agree

22:58.000 --> 23:00.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with them.

23:00.133 --> 23:03.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And so how
does the town respond when
they see these women picketing

23:03.300 --> 23:04.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
policies of the
Trump administration?

23:04.966 --> 23:07.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: Not well.

23:07.000 --> 23:11.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They have gotten a lot
of pushback from the
town, from everyone from
the local fraternity

23:13.366 --> 23:16.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
brothers at the nearby college,
to their husbands, to their
neighbors, to people at the high

23:17.366 --> 23:19.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
school,.

23:19.000 --> 23:23.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Some of their kids have
been made fun of for
the women protesting.

23:25.300 --> 23:27.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Other women go home at night
and their husbands get after
them for appearing on the front

23:27.333 --> 23:29.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
page with a protest sign.

23:29.733 --> 23:34.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, for them, I think
it's a constant struggle
to keep protesting, in
light of the reaction

23:36.166 --> 23:38.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that they are getting.

23:38.200 --> 23:40.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: As you point
out, a lot of these women
were not engaged in this way

23:40.900 --> 23:42.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
before this election.

23:42.000 --> 23:44.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: Absolutely not.

23:44.100 --> 23:48.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Most of them told me the only
political participation they had
up until this point was voting.

23:49.166 --> 23:50.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Most of them had never
held a protest sign.

23:50.233 --> 23:51.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This was very new to them.

23:51.766 --> 23:54.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think what is interesting is,
this wasn't an organized thing.

23:54.333 --> 23:58.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A lot of these women just
decided individually that after
the election they wanted to do

23:58.833 --> 24:00.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
something, they wanted
to go out and protest.

24:00.966 --> 24:04.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They went to the county -- in
front of the county Courthouse
and held a sign, and they

24:04.333 --> 24:06.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
