against Trump's policies
around the country.

25:23.300 --> 25:26.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And speaking
of around the country, is
this a microcosm of something

25:26.100 --> 25:28.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that is happening elsewhere?

25:28.700 --> 25:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH FLOCK: I do
think this -- Buckhannon
is -- it's one small town
where this is happening,

25:34.166 --> 25:36.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
but there are a lot of
indications that there
are women who are doing
this across the country.

25:36.866 --> 25:41.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, 11,000 women are
considering running for office
for the first time, according to

25:41.566 --> 25:43.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
EMILY's List, after
Trump's election.

25:43.966 --> 25:48.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Obviously, the women's march
was a huge show of interest
by women in participating.

25:50.833 --> 25:52.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the Indivisible
groups have been spreading
across the country.

25:52.866 --> 25:54.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think there's
6,000 of them now.

25:54.866 --> 25:59.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And after the story came out,
a lot of women from rural
areas wrote and said that, this

26:01.700 --> 26:04.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
really resonated with me and
this is what is going on in our
town as well, in Pennsylvania,

26:04.166 --> 26:08.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Ohio, across Appalachia,
and basically said
we're also protesting.

26:08.000 --> 26:09.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It is really hard for us here.

26:09.966 --> 26:12.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is really isolating, because
