States will pull out of
the Paris climate accord?

26:49.966 --> 26:52.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What did you make of it?

26:52.000 --> 26:55.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: In immediate
impact, Judy, it probably means
less in the American environment

26:58.666 --> 27:03.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
than the rules and
regulations already repealed
by his administration
and by his EPA that

27:06.533 --> 27:10.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
were put in force, emissions
controlled by President Obama.

27:10.833 --> 27:15.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, in a larger sense,
it belies and reveals
that president's
sense about the world.

27:18.400 --> 27:21.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The world is a dangerous,
sinister place.

27:21.400 --> 27:22.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There's conspiracies.

27:22.900 --> 27:26.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Other countries are not
our friends, are partners.

27:26.700 --> 27:28.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Everything is transactional.

27:28.266 --> 27:30.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There are no fixed values.

27:30.266 --> 27:34.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We saw that, I thought most
dramatically, at NATO, where
the president showed an absolute

27:36.600 --> 27:40.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
absence of any historical
understanding of
American exceptionalism.

27:40.500 --> 27:45.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, as one who frankly
subscribes to it that
three times in the
20th century the United

27:47.433 --> 27:50.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
States saved the world from
totalitarianism, twice in World
Wars, once in the Cold War,

27:53.300 --> 27:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and 124,965 American graves
around the world in cemeteries,
and 94,000 still missing.

27:59.800 --> 28:01.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I just don't understand.

28:01.333 --> 28:03.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The president knows
that it was for values.

28:03.633 --> 28:06.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And when NATO has made
mistakes, we have made mistakes.

28:06.633 --> 28:08.966 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have been guilty of hubris.

28:08.966 --> 28:13.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the world is a much
better place because of the
United States' leadership.

28:13.166 --> 28:18.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this was an example of
the United States working with
other nations for a common good

28:19.466 --> 28:20.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to preserve our planet.

28:20.933 --> 28:23.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And he just turned
his back on it.

28:23.066 --> 28:25.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What did you make
of the president's decision and
his argument for why he did it?

28:25.666 --> 28:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, well,
I sort of agree with Mark.

28:27.033 --> 28:28.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It was nice to have
an American century.

28:28.433 --> 28:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We were a superpower once.

28:29.700 --> 28:31.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And now we're headed
the way of Portugal.

28:31.700 --> 28:36.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No, it was --
environmentally, I can't
get super excited about it.

28:36.500 --> 28:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it was a
setback for the cause of
addressing global warming.

28:40.233 --> 28:44.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But, as we have heard
many times, it was a
voluntary agreement.

28:44.633 --> 28:48.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so this -- and we have done
a very good job, because of
natural gas and fracking and

28:48.433 --> 28:51.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
other things, of reducing
emissions over the
last five years or so.

28:51.733 --> 28:55.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I presume the market
will still work and the
emissions will still come down.

28:55.800 --> 29:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so we -- Donald Trump could
have addressed his concerns
about coal workers and stayed

29:00.200 --> 29:01.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the Paris accords.

29:01.133 --> 29:02.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There is nothing block.

29:02.133 --> 29:03.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It was totally voluntary.

29:03.866 --> 29:05.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So this wasn't about
global warming.

29:05.466 --> 29:07.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This wasn't about
the environment.

29:07.500 --> 29:12.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was about sticking a thumb
in the eye of polite society,
the elites, the globalists.

29:14.333 --> 29:18.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was a Steve Bannon-led
thing designed to change
America's role in the world.

29:18.333 --> 29:23.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And so, to me, the
effect is much worse
on the global diplomacy
and the idea of a world

29:24.900 --> 29:27.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
order than it is, at
least in the short-term,
about climate change.

29:27.733 --> 29:29.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And the effects, I
think, are ruinous.

29:29.766 --> 29:33.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
You can't lead the world
and stick your thumb in
the eye of the world.

29:33.666 --> 29:37.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People -- if you act extremely
selfishly to other people, they
will start acting extremely

29:37.433 --> 29:38.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
selfishly to you.

29:38.900 --> 29:41.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that is about to happen.

29:41.133 --> 29:45.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so as the idea that America
could lead the world and
should influence the world and

29:45.766 --> 29:50.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should have friendship with
other powerful nations in the
world, that's an idea that

29:50.066 --> 29:52.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
took a big hit this week.

29:52.233 --> 29:55.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, as
we famously heard him
say, yesterday, Mark,
the president said,

29:55.533 --> 29:59.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm here to represent the
people of Pittsburgh, and
not the people of Paris.

29:59.033 --> 30:04.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Yes, no, it
was a nice alliterative
line that didn't have
much relevance in reality,

30:05.900 --> 30:10.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pittsburgh having supported
Hillary Clinton and
basically being a green city.

30:13.066 --> 30:16.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I think it was a
political statement.

30:16.400 --> 30:21.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
One can say, in defense
of the president, I
guess, he kept his word.

30:22.566 --> 30:25.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He hasn't been known as
a truth-teller always.

30:25.033 --> 30:28.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
No one has confused him with
George Washington on veracity.

30:28.833 --> 30:33.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But he kept his word
on the Trans-Pacific
treaty, trade treaty.

30:33.633 --> 30:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He kept his word on NATO and
that he was going to belittle
it, or at least diminish it.

30:39.600 --> 30:41.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And he kept his word here.

30:41.166 --> 30:44.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think that was probably
the strongest argument inside.

30:44.833 --> 30:46.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes.

30:46.900 --> 30:50.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yes, I'm just struck by the fact
that his is an administration
driven solely by resentment.

30:52.933 --> 30:55.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He will side with the Steve
Bannon side if that position
will alienate the people he

